2. Split data

Training and testing sets

overfitting() . . . .

# Split 80% / 20%
set.seed(123)
split <- initial_split(data = insurance, prop = 0.80, strata = charges)

# Training set
train_set <- training(split)

# Testing set
test_set <- testing(split)

Cross validation

5 partitions() .

set.seed(123)
folds <- vfold_cv(train_set, strata = charges, v = 5)

3. Preprocessing recipe

recipe .

  • response variable() .
  • categorical variable( ) .
  • .
  • Dummy .
  • interactions() .
recipe <- 
  recipe(charges ~ ., data = train_set) %>% 
  step_log(all_outcomes()) %>% 
  step_mutate(is_obsessive = 
                if_else(bmi > 30, "Yes", "No") %>% 
                factor(levels = c("Yes", "No"))) %>% 
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors()) %>% 
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>% 
  step_interact(terms = ~ smoker_yes:age) %>% 
  step_interact(terms = ~ smoker_yes:bmi)

4. Model spec( )

# Random forest spec (   )
rf_spec <- rand_forest(
  mtry = tune(),      #  : mtry (  )
  trees = tune(),     #  : trees ( )
  min_n = tune()       #  : min_n (    )
) %>%
  set_engine(
    "ranger",          #   (ranger  )
    num.threads = 7,   #    
    importance = "impurity"  #    
  ) %>%
  set_mode("regression")  #  :  

# Ranfom forest workflow
rf_Wf <- workflow() %>% 
  add_recipe(recipe) %>%   #       recipe  
  add_model(rf_spec)       #

Setting grid

. (https://www.tmwr.org/grid-search.html)

# Space-filling designs grid
rf_grid <- 
  grid_latin_hypercube(
    min_n(), 
    mtry(range = c(4, 9)), 
    trees(), 
    size = 80)

grid visualize() .

Tuning Hyperparameters

# Lets use 7 cores for this process
doParallel::registerDoParallel(cores = 7)

set.seed(123)
tune_res <- 
  rf_Wf %>% 
  tune_grid(
    resamples = folds, grid = rf_grid, 
    metrics = metric_set(rmse, mae, rsq)
    )
